<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=0 WIDTH="95%"><TR ><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#F0DCA0" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">E-Hyvel</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hi there!<BR>I'm flat broke, so I'm still waiting for my paycheck before I can buy this game, but I loved the demo.<BR>Now I think I have checked almost all Div Div coverage on the net, but I can't find any statistics on the different skill(level)s. While playing Diablo II, I used to stare at the statistics of the different skills for hours, trying to come up with the most effective/interesting combination of skills for my next character. Can anybody post some information about the effects of the skills for different levels, or show me where I can find such information? It would really help me pass the time until I can buy the game myself...<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Warhammer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sadly even the manual does not cover your need, it just gives a general description of the skill, even the in game description is scarce: The only ranks, you can view a detailed description of, are the current rank and the next one.<P>If you have a particular skill you want to now more about I could help.</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">E-Hyvel</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">It's a real shame: manuals hardly ever cover the needs for the Statistic Freak. I am interested in all skills, but the most interesting would be skills like meteorstrike & other magic skills, since they (unlike for example augment damage) do not depend on items for their effectiveness.</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">CDR Seadog</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">  My recommendation would be to at least inverst in Meteorstrike, and Wisdom (Meteorstrike for a cheap and easy ranged weapon, and Wisdom for the added boost to experience points).</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lazy Ben</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You can find/buy quite a lot of spellbooks.  I didn't put a single point in magic but finished the game knowing more skillpoints worth of it then my other abilities.  So even if you want to learn a spell to the max, don't.  You might find a spell book 10 mins later and it will really annoy you.</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Nightfire</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I too would be very interested in a listing of all the skills at the various skills levels, with prerequisites, effects and cost. Wouldn't that be a good project for one of the fansites?  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">E-Hyvel</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I only know this list that was extracted from the demo:<BR> <A HREF="http://www.footprint.be/divinity/skills.htm" TARGET=_blank>http://www.footprint.be/divinity/skills.htm</A> <P>Can anybody confirm if any of these stats have remained the same?</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Viper</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">that would be nice idd but the prerequisite there is that you need to have the game.